<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-819] NPE when no metadata is defined for a persistent class</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-819</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The persistent class was specified in the persistence.xml under &amp;lt;class&amp;gt;, but persistence metadata was not specified for the class, either through annotation or the orm.xml. A NPE was thrown. We need a better message.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue was reported in the user forum by post &lt;a href=&quot;http://n2.nabble.com/NullPointerException-when-calling-createEntityManager-on--EntityManagerFactory-td1621881.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://n2.nabble.com/NullPointerException-when-calling-createEntityManager-on--EntityManagerFactory-td1621881.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
